Browser Toolbox bundles the EFF Large Wordlist for passphrase generation.
"EFF Large Wordlist" by the Electronic Frontier Foundation is licensed under
CC BY 3.0 US (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/us/).

Vendored libraries (the file in assets/vendor/ is byte-identical to the npm
release of the version listed below; when upgrading, re-copy from node_modules
and update both this version and the matching pin in package.json):
- qrcode-generator 2.0.4 (MIT) — Kazuhiko Arase
- piexifjs 1.0.6 (MIT) — hMatoba
  (piexif.js self-reports `that.version = "1.0.4"` internally; that is an
  upstream labeling bug — the shipped file is the official 1.0.6 release.)
- jsQR 1.4.0 (Apache License 2.0) — Cosmo Wolfe and contributors
  (https://github.com/cozmo/jsQR). Used to decode uploaded QR images in the
  browser. The distributed jsQR.js carries no inline license header and upstream
  ships no NOTICE file, so this entry is the required attribution; the full
  Apache-2.0 license text is at https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.
- zxcvbn 4.4.2 (MIT) — Dropbox, Inc. (Daniel Lowe Wheeler and contributors)
  (https://github.com/dropbox/zxcvbn). Used to rate typed-password strength and
  gate the Password Vault's master password, entirely in the browser.
